# Matiaullah Khatibi Portfolio

This is my personal portfolio website showcasing my skills, education, and experience in web development.

## Table of Contents

- [Description](#description)
- [Features](#features)
- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)

## Description

The Matiaullah Khatibi Portfolio is a website designed to present my skills, education, and work experience in an organized and visually appealing manner. It provides an overview of my background, including my education history, work experience, and contact information.

## Features

- Introduction section with a brief overview of myself and my journey in web development.
- Education section showcasing my educational background.
- Experience section highlighting my work history and responsibilities.
- Contact section with my email address and links to my social media profiles.
- Responsive design to ensure optimal viewing experience across different devices.

## Installation

To run this project locally, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git`
2. Navigate to the project directory: `cd your-repo`
3. Open the `index.html` file in your preferred web browser.

## Usage

Simply open the website in a web browser to explore the different sections and learn more about my skills and experience. Use the navigation menu at the top to access specific sections of the website.

## Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript
- Font Awesome (for social media icons)

## Contributing

Contributions are welcome! If you would like to contribute to this project, please follow these steps:

1. Fork the repository.
2. Create a new branch: `git checkout -b your-branch-name`
3. Make your changes and commit them: `git commit -m 'Add your commit message'`
4. Push to your branch: `git push origin your-branch-name`
5. Submit a pull request.
